Spring Security

> Implemented using servlet filters in the background
>Two method of securing a web app : Declarative and Programmatic
>Servlet filters are used to pre-process / post-process web requests.
>Servlet filters can route web requests based on security logic.
>Spring provide a bulk of security functionality with servelet filters.

Declarative Security
>Define app security constraints in configuration (java config(@Configuration ,no xml) or XML).

Programmatic Security
>Spring provides an API for custom application coding.
>Provide Greater customization for specific app requirements.(we can add personal security implementation logic/plugin).

Different Login Methods
>HTTP Basic Authentication
>Default Login Form
>Custom Login Form
